s based on the\nlast quarterly or semi-annual declaration\nUnless otherwise noted special or extra\ndividends are not Included.\na Also extra or extras, e Declared or\npaid so far this year no regular rat*,\nf Payable in stock g Paid last year,\nb Cash or stock k Accumulated dividend\npaid or declared this year n With war\nrants. xw Without warrants, war War\nrants.\nTREASURY HEADS PLAN\nNO FURTHER BORROWING\nBy the Associated Press.\nSecretary Morgenthau said yester\nday the Treasury contemplates no bor\nrowing March 15, except through the\nsale of some discount bills previously\nannounced.\nA total of $450,000,000 of Treasury\nbills maturing around March 15 will\nbe paid off in cash from income tax\ncollections, Morgethau said, and hold\ners of $455,000,000 of 3 per cent\nTreasury notes maturing will be of\nfered a new security in exchange.\nThe bill issues to which the Secre\ntary referred are a series of $50,000,\n000 weekly offers which began yester\nday and will continue until $200,000,\n000 to $300,000,000 have been raised.\nThe number of weeks that the bills\nwill be offered will depend upon the\nsuccess of March 15 tax collections.\nDIVIDENDS ANNOUNCED\nNEW YORK. March 1.\u2014Dividends de\nclared, prepared by the Standard Statistics\nCo.:\nReduced.\nPe- stock of Pay\nRate riod. record, able.\nNat Standard Co. 12Vic 3-1 ft 4-1\nKlelnert Rubber _ 10c 3-15 3-30\nMohawk Carpet _ ..25c 3-10 3-15\nNo Action Taken.\nBendix Aviation Corp.\nJohns-Manville\nMcCahan Sue Ref dc Molasses 72 pf.\nMead Corn.\nRayonier. Inc.\nG. Krueger Brew.\n8terehi Bros.\nSterchi Bros. 2d pfd.\nReaular.\nAm Hdwr CorD _..25c Q 3-12 4-1\nAm Safety Razor 50c Q 3-10 3-30\nAtl Ref Co 4'. Df A $1 Q 4-5 5-2\nBal Co 62 cum of A *1.50 Q 2-28 3-15\nDo. 62 cum pf $1.50 Q 3-31 4-15\nBorne Scrymser 50c 3-21 4-15\nBrazilian Traction\nLap 6r, pf $1.50 Q 3-15 4-1\nBriggs Strat Corp 75c 3-3 3-15\nCocoa-Cola Co _ 50c 3-12 4-1\nCon Ed N Y $5 pf $1.25 Q 4-1 5-2\nCrowell Pub Co 75c Q 3-14 3-24\nDixie Ice C