reat Britain in dollars, others in\ncents.\nGreat Britain\u2014Demand. 5 01*,: cables,\n5.01 60-day bills. 5.00\u2019\u00ab. France\u2014\nDemand. 3.26*,: cables 3.2B\u00bb\u00bb. Italy\u2014\nDemand. 5.26',: cables 5.26'.,.\nDemands\u2014Belgium. 16.98\u2019,: Germany,\nfree 40.47'*; registered. 20.55; travel,\n25.00; Holland. 55.97: Norway. 25.22;\nSweden. 25.88: Denmark. 22.41: Finland.\n2.22',: Switzerland. 23.23',: Hpain. un\nquoted; Portugal. 4.50\u2019a: Greece. 92',:\nPoland. 19.00; Czechoslovakia. 3 Si5,:\nYugoslavia. 2.35: Austria. 18.95n; Hun\ngary 19.93: Rumania. ,74V\u00bb: Argentina.\n33.47n: Brazil (free). S.oon: Tokio. 29.03:\nShanghai. 29.76: Hong Kong. 31.45: Mex\nico City. 27.80: Montreal in New York.\n100.00: New York In Montreal. 100.00.\nn Nominal.\nFOBEIGN MABKETS.\nLONDON March 1 MY\u2014Trading In\ntoday's stock market continued on a small\nscale and after an easier tone in the\nearly dealings prices rallied from their low\nprices Trans-Atlantic issues were oft\nfractions to a point and home rails were\nheavy. Industrial shares were mixed, with\nsteels, tobaccos and rayons In supply. Oils\nand mining issues sold at lower levels,\nwhile British funds and rubbers remained\nquiet.\nPARIS.\u2014Price movements were mixed\nin the Bourse and industrial shares showed\nfractional changes in both directions at\nthe close. Suez Canal lost 145 francs and\nBank of France issue was down 60. Rentes\nfinished 35 centimes lower to 5 higher.\nInternational securities were heavy.\nSTATEMENT OP THE CONDITION\nOF THE\nPennsylvania\nIndemnity Corporation\nOI Philadelphia. Pennsylvania, on the 31st\nday 01 December 1937. as required under\nSection 647 of the Code of Law for the\nDistret of Columbia.\nINCOME.\nNet premiums Sl.8fi3.759.83\nTotal Interest and renta_ 5fi.159.fll\nOther Income _ 135.783.05\nTotal Income__#2.055.702.81\nDISBURSEMENTS.\nNet amount paia policyhold\ners for losses _. $727,762.95\nAll other disbursements_ 1.153,894.18\nTotal disbursements_